node.text: #ad Earlier this year, the good guys at @lumixuk asked me to create a video capturing my interpretation of light and shadow with the new Lumix S5, and so I headed to my favourite part of Bali to do just that! Meandering through these quaint villages as the sun comes up is where I’m happiest, and the S5 made light work of the piercing rays that engulf the villages here on any clear morning. If you know anything about me, you’ll know that I am a videographer newbie - guilty as charged. However, the dynamic range blew me away with its ability to retain the highlights and the 5-axis IBIS made handheld shots a walk in the park while we were on the move. @thefreedomcomplex and I had an absolute blast putting this one together, and as it’s a first of sorts for me, I’d love to get your thoughts on the video!  #LUMIX #MovingImagesForward #LUMIXS5 #ShotOnLumix

node.text: #ad Earlier this year, the good guys at @lumixuk asked me to create a video capturing my interpretation of light and shadow with the new Lumix S5, and so I headed to my favourite part of Bali to do just that! Meandering through these quaint villages as the sun comes up is where I’m happiest, and the S5 made light work of the piercing rays that engulf the villages here on any clear morning. If you know anything about me, you’ll know that I am a videographer newbie - guilty as charged. However, the dynamic range blew me away with its ability to retain the highlights and the 5-axis IBIS made handheld shots a walk in the park while we were on the move. @thefreedomcomplex and I had an absolute blast putting this one together, and as it’s a first of sorts for me, I’d love to get your thoughts on the video!  #LUMIX #MovingImagesForward #LUMIXS5 #ShotOnLumix

node.text: Out of all the places we visited in Croatia, the source of the Cetina River was my favourite! Having visited twice over two consecutive days, we lucked out on the latter and had the place entirely to ourselves. While the 5°C water originally put me off, Soph did manage to convince me to take a dip with her! It was truly freezing, but once you had your breath under control it was surprisingly therapeutic. Would you dare to swim here? 👁🍉 @croatiafulloflife #croatiafulloflife

node.text: Hello from Croatia! node.text:
If you’ve been following me for a while now, you’ll know that things were non-stop pre-pandemic, and even then that seems to be putting it mildly. As a full-time travel photographer, if someone had told me in March 2020 that I’d spend the next 17 months in one place, then I’d have done everything in my power to reject the idea and to prevent it from happening. 

From continually meeting new and interesting people, to experiencing the vibrant cultures that shaped them, to working back-to-back with dream clients and constantly adjusting to changing time zones and endless long haul flights - that’s where I thrived, or at least I thought I did.

Without the old routine, I’d often find myself wondering what the hell I’d do to fill the gaps. While I didn’t expect it, the serious amount of time I’ve had to recharge and reflect has led me to the conclusion that full-time travel was perhaps the biggest distraction in my life and left me little to no time to work on myself, which is something I think we should all prioritise. That in itself continues to challenge me, and is something I’m still working on as I write this. 

With that said, I found a whole new love and appreciation for the island in places I never expected, and is for now where @sophiapope and I gleefully call home. 

Can anyone here relate? I know it’s been a strangely mad time in recent years, but just know that irrespective of your current situation, you’re not alone in this and that my door is always open if you need me! 👨🏾‍🌾 🌊
